   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER TWO IN HIS INCARNATION 2 Scripture Reading: Matt 1:21, 23; Rom 8:3; 1 Pet 1:19-20; Heb 9:26, 28, 12; 2:14; 1 Tim 1:15; 1 John 4:9 OUTLINE The issue of the incarnation: Jesus Jehovah our Savior Matt 1:21.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Emmanuel God with us Matt 1:23.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The God-man the complete God and the perfect man.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The purpose of the incarnation: To bring God into man.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>To make God man that man may become God in life and nature but not in the Godhead.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To mingle God with man that God and man may be one.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>To accomplish God's redemption for man Rom 8:3; 1 Pet 1:18-20; Heb 9:26, 28, 12; 2:14.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>To carry out God's salvation in man 1 Tim 1:15.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To impart the divine life into man 1 John 4:9.</S>
   </TEXT>
